{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀτῑμ-άζω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> <b>-άσω</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 917 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 465a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἠτίμασα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 49, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 292e, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἠτίμακα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.31, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 266d\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>perfect</i> ἠτίμασμαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 20, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 219d, 4th c.BC: Ephorus Historicus “fragment” \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] 3.21B.: <i>aorist</i> ἠτιμάσθην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 123.5, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 931b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> ἀτιμασθήσομαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1068, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1081\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: (ἄτιμος):—<b>hold in no honour, esteem lightly,</b> with <i>accusative</i>, once in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.450 ἀτιμάζεσκε δ᾽ ἄκοιτιν\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”, τούσδε γ᾽ ἀτιμάζει κατὰ δῆμον 6.283; οἶκον ἀτιμάζοντες ἔδουσιν 21.332, compare 427; ἀ. τοκῆας 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 821: frequently in Trag., 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 1023, “Eu.” 712, 917, +others; μή μ᾽ ἀτιμάσας γένῃ 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista Trag.20 (= [prev. author]Comedy texts 80), compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 40.26, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. καὶ κολάζειν, opposed to ἐπαινεῖν καὶ τιμᾶν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.20; τὴν ἀνθρωπίνην ἀσθένειαν ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 107b, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>bring dishonour upon,</b> τὴν πόλιν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.31: with _accusative_ _cognate_, ἔπη ἃ ἀτιμάζεις πόλιν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] the words thou <b>speakest in dishonour of</b> the city, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 340\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>suffer dishonour, insult,</b> etc., πρός τινος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 123.5, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.61; τινί 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1342; οὐκ ἀτιμασθήσομαι [prev. author] “OT” 1081, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.74\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῷ γεγενημένῳ <b>put to shame by</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.27: with _neuter_ _plural_, ἀνάξι᾽ ἠτιμασμένη 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 943. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>treat as unworthy of,</b> μηδ᾽ ἀτιμάσῃς λόγου (i.e. ἐμέ) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 783\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; μή μ᾽ ἀτιμάσῃς ὧν σε προστρέπω φράσαι, ={τούτων ἅ σε πρ. φρ}., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 49, compare “Ant.” 22. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with <i>infinitive</i>, ὦ θάνατε Παιάν, μή μ᾽ ἀτιμάσῃς μολεῖν <b>do</b> not <b>deem</b> me <b>unworthy</b> of thy visit, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 255.1\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; μήτοι μ᾽ ἀτιμάσῃς τὸ μὴ οὐ θανεῖν σὺν σοί <b>deem</b> me not <b>unworthy</b> to die, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 544\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but also οὐκ ἀτιμάσω θεοὺς προσειπεῖν <b>will</b> not <b>disdain</b> to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 608, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 182c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in legal sense, <b>disfranchise,</b> ὑπὸ τῆς πόλεως ἠτιμασμένος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Ephorus Historicus [same place] \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; at Rome, of the Censors, <b>punish with ignominia,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 38.13.\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0818","accentedUnicode":"ἀτιμάζω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0819","matchingForm":"ἀτιμία","stepTransliteration":"atimia","gloss":"dishonour","_zh_tw_Gloss":"羞辱","_es_Gloss":"deshonra ","_zh_Gloss":"羞辱"},{"strongNumber":"G0820","matchingForm":"ἄτιμος","stepTransliteration":"atimos","gloss":"dishonored","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不被尊敬, 被藐視","_es_Gloss":"deshonrado","_zh_Gloss":"不被尊敬, 被藐视"},{"strongNumber":"G1784","matchingForm":"ἔντιμος","stepTransliteration":"entimos","gloss":"valued/honored","_zh_tw_Gloss":"所寶貴","_es_Gloss":"preciado/honrado","_zh_Gloss":"所宝贵"},{"strongNumber":"G2472","matchingForm":"ἰσότιμος","stepTransliteration":"isotimos","gloss":"equally valuable","_zh_tw_Gloss":"一樣寶貴","_es_Gloss":"igualmente valioso","_zh_Gloss":"一样宝贵"},{"strongNumber":"G5091","matchingForm":"τιμάω","stepTransliteration":"timaō","gloss":"to honor","_zh_tw_Gloss":"尊敬","_es_Gloss":"honrar","_zh_Gloss":"尊敬"},{"strongNumber":"G5092","matchingForm":"τιμή","stepTransliteration":"timē","gloss":"honor","_zh_tw_Gloss":"尊貴","_es_Gloss":"honor","_zh_Gloss":"尊贵"},{"strongNumber":"G5093","matchingForm":"τίμιος","stepTransliteration":"timios","gloss":"precious","_zh_tw_Gloss":"寶","_es_Gloss":"precioso","_zh_Gloss":"宝"},{"strongNumber":"G5094","matchingForm":"τιμι